    "y 1 1 THE MARKETS Furniehed each Thursday afternoon at five oclock by the Farmers Elevator on the G N tracks in Bowbells Wheat No 1 134 Durum wheat 133 Flax 167 Rye 92 Barley 50 Oats 43 Eggs 14 Butter 20 Potatoes 50 If you have a farm for sale list it with the Burke County invest ment Co Bowbells N D The ladies aid society of the M E church meets on Thursday of next week with Mrs A H Beer Everybody invited Remember the dance at the Roy al Teatre next Monday evening A big crowd is sure to be present and a royal time is assured all who come Be sure to inspect the large and complete millinery stock of Mrs Johnson in Bowbells Her line this year is more complete than over The Donovan Bros hardware Ltore the fore part of the week re ceived a shipment of a half a car load of nails woven wire and barb wire The county commissioners will hold their quarterly meeting com mencing on Monday of next week and will look after the regular routine of business Among other things bids will be considered for the furnishing of"
